Rating: 4
Really good recipe. I used 1% milk and it turned out fine. I added some marjarom in addition to the thyme and threw in some shredded swiss cheese. I also added bread crumbs with butter as a topping-- but I think it would be great without any of these additions or changes.

Rating: 4
Great recipe, and I don't even like turnips! I did tweak the recipe slightly. I replaced the half and half with whole milk, but kept the heavy cream. For the sauce, I started with a roux, added the milk and cream until it thickened up a little. Added the aromatics and spices with a dash of nutmeg, 1/2 cup of grated Parmigiano-Reggiano, and a small cube of fontina I had sitting in the fridge. Cooked in a square pyrex dish. I sliced the turnips paper thin so I wouldn't be overwhelmed by them and did a mix of potato and white sweet potato. Delicious!

