Rating: 3
What's wrong with a little richness? That's why this gratin was so tasty. The turnips were from my garden, and they add a sweetness to the dish that you just won't get with plain potatoes. I lightened it by using all half and half, and served it at a spring celebration feast with roast lamb, braised salmon on wilted spinach, new peas, cauliflower puree and a mixed green salad. Heart healthy? Probably not, but my family and guests (I fed 16)enjoyed an exceptional meal in wonderful company. The chocolate cake with fresh strawberries and cream was rocking too.

