Rating: 3
Down home comfort food and very tasty. A nice variation on scalloped potatoes. I used rutabagas rather than turnips - personal preference. The thyme was a good complement and I also added a few dashes of nutmeg for more depth of flavour. Yes, it is rich as it is meant to be. Considering it serves 8, each serving contains approx. 1/3 cup of cream which really isn't so bad on an occasional basis. At first glance, any cook knows this is calorie/fat laden, but all things in moderation. We can't always eat twigs, pebbles and leaves! If this recipe appeals to you, make it and enjoy this guilty pleasure. Then, skip dessert to ease your conscience. Cheers!

